Yeah, except one little thing.  Most people won't cancel their EQ accounts to try out another game.  Besides which, how many competing games have the drawing power of the Star Wars name? Even have the drawing power of the EQ name? If there were a glut of worthy competitors, you might have a point.  Truth is, there are not any competitors that have the lineage and recognition that they do and Sony knows it.   <br>
<br>
 I think they're betting with the retention of customers they saw with EQ that people who get bored with EQ are most likely going to at least TRY EQ2.  I'd say that's actually a pretty safe assumption.  As much as people bitch about EQ, they still play it.  It's got a more lucrative economy than most third world countries for god's sake.  A few tweaks here and there to the things people bitch about the most and tell me that most EQ'ers aren't gonna play it. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm not suggesting that there are a bunch of evil suits at Sony plotting the demise of EQ as we speak. But it is rather naive to think they aren't looking ahead to insure the success of EQ2 and SWG by drawing a large number of EQ players to them.  Maybe I'm just a tad too cynical, but I think the fact that they just trivialized 85% of the games content in the course of one expansion could be a step in that direction.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=casmx>CasmX</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.rpgrevelation.com/board/levels/12.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1872.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> imo, all they did was add 2 intersting spell lines that they can add on later too. For ppl at those lvls, it'll be great. for players above that, I'd expect to see 'add ons' to those spell lines <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573070" target="top">Casm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=znailvh>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1872.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left 